    <title>
        Client Agreement - Template
    </title>
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Header (appears on first page content; for repeating header use PHP in dompdf) -->
    <div class="section" style="font-size:11px;">
         <p class="section-title"><strong>8. Validity</strong><br/>
        This agreement is a one-time agreement between the firm and the client, and valid for 11 months.  During this period, all service-related transactions between the two parties will be governed by the service start and end dates specified in the service invoice, and a separate agreement will not be required for each transaction; the terms and conditions of this agreement will apply. The service invoice will serve as proof of the service's validity.
        </p>
        <p class="section-title"><strong>9. Consideration &amp; Payment Terms</strong><br/>
        The Client agrees to make all payments via account payee crossed cheque, demand draft, or direct credit to the Research Analyst's designated bank account through NEFT, RTGS, IMPS, Payment Gateway or valid UPI. Payments are only accepted in the bank accounts listed on the Research Analyst's official website {{ra_website}}
        . The Research Analyst shall not be liable for any payments made to accounts other than those specified on the website.
        </p>
        <p>a. The Client shall make payments only in the name of “ <b> {{ra_brand}} </b> ” through official banking channels as communicated by the Research Analyst or mentioned on the website <b> {{ra_website}} </b>.</p>
        <p>b. No payment shall be made to any individual employee, agent, or personal bank account.</p>
        <p>c. Any such payment, if made, shall not be recognized by the Research Analyst and the Client shall bear sole responsibility.</p>
        <p>d. The Client shall not communicate with any employee/representative of the Research Analyst over personal WhatsApp numbers, personal emails, or other informal channels.</p>
        <p>e. All official communication shall only be through designated official email IDs, portals, and telephone numbers provided by the Research Analyst or its website <b> {{ra_website}} </b> .</p>
        <p>f. The Client agrees not to share Aadhaar OTP, Bank OTP, or any confidential code with anyone including employees of the Research Analyst.</p>
        <p class="section-title"><strong>10. Optional Centralised Fee Collection Mechanism</strong><br/>
        There is an optional ‘Centralized Fee Collection Mechanism for Investment Advisors and Research Analysts’ (CeFCoM) for fee payments. The Research Analyst has presently not opted for the same and once the Research Analyst gets registered for it, then thereafter said mechanism will be available for the client.
        </p>
        <p class="section-title"><strong>11. Fee Structure</strong><br/>
        The Client agrees to pay a fee for the services to Research Analyst . All the details relating to services will be governed by service invoice. Fee shall be charged in accordance with SEBI RA Regulations and master circular. All applicable taxes (GST, etc.) shall be borne by the Client only.</p>
        <p class="section-title"><strong>12. Confidentiality</strong><br/>
        Both Parties shall maintain confidentiality of information shared and comply with provisions of the Information Technology Act, 2000 and SEBI RA Regulations regarding client data protection. Research Analyst shall be responsible for maintenance of client accounts and data as mandated under the SEBI (Research Analyst) Regulations, 2014.
        </p>
        <p class="section-title"><strong>13. Means Of Communication</strong><br/>
        The Research Analyst will provide recommendations via SMS/WhatsApp. The Client shall only accept recommendations received through these specified mediums. The Research Analyst shall not be liable for any communications received by the Client through other means. Additionally, the Client acknowledges communications via email through <b>{{ra_email}}</b> or <b>{{ra_website}}</b> domain name only. Research Analyst will not be liable for any email which is been received by client from any other domain name.
        </p>
        <p class="section-title"><strong>14. Record Keeping</strong><br/>
        The RA shall maintain all records related to client communications and recommendations as per Regulation 25 of the SEBI (Research Analysts) Regulations, 2014.
        </p>
        <p class="section-title"><strong>15. Consent as per SEBI Regulations</strong><br/>
        The Client, having understood the services, scope, fee structure, and limitations of the Research Analyst, hereby provides informed consent to avail the services, in line with Regulation 22 of SEBI (Research Analyst) Regulations, 2014.
        </p>
        <p class="section-title"><strong>16. Electronic Execution (Aadhaar e-Sign)</strong><br/>
           a.This Agreement shall be digitally executed by the Client using Aadhaar e-Sign through the DGO platform, confirming that:<br/>
       b.The Client has carefully read all the clauses of this Agreement,<br/>
        c.The Client voluntarily gives consent to this Agreement,<br/>
        d.The Client digitally signs this Agreement without any undue influence or misrepresentation.</p>
        </div>
</body>
</html>